But it is reward for consistent excellence for Sale this season and  working with Jonny Wilkinson’s former mentor Steve Black to improve his off-field behaviour — last season’s drunken run-in with a double decker bus was the last in a litany of misdemeanours.

With Myler and Farrell likely to be involved in the Aviva Premiership final on May 31 and therefore forced to miss the opening Test in Auckland on June 7, there is every chance the most talented English player of his generation could win a long overdue eighth cap.

‘I’ve taken a lot of feedback from the coaching team at Sale and Steve Diamond and Brian Redpath are good judges of character and talent,’ added Lancaster. ‘I spoke to Danny ahead of the Six Nations and gave him some areas to work on and he’s gone away and done that. 

