It is hard not to feel sympathy for the head coach, who played no part in the fixture scheduling —described by England flanker Tom Wood as ‘ridiculous’ — which leaves the winners of this  weekend’s Premiership semi-finals knowing they will have played themselves out of the tour.

‘It’s hard to disagree with Tom and the way he articulated it,’ said Lancaster. ‘He, alongside everyone else, is frustrated by the situation. We get very few opportunities to go to a country like New Zealand and play against them and you want to go with you best side.’

Whether Cipriani is part of that group remains to be seen.

